</head>
<body>

  <header class="page-header">
    <div class="page-header-main">
      <h1>Vegetable Shepherd’s Pie</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        A plant-based twist on classic shepherd’s pie with roasted cauliflower puree and hearty vegetables.
      </p>

      <div class="recipe-meta">
        <span class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>Main Dishes</span>
        <span class="badge">Baked</span>
        <span class="badge">Approx. 1 hr</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <nav class="link-row" aria-label="Primary">
    <a href="./">All Recipes</a>
    <a href="#" aria-current="page">Vegetable Shepherd’s Pie</a>
    <button class="btn btn-sm" onclick="window.print()">Print</button>
  </nav>

  <main class="layout">

    <aside class="sidebar card" aria-label="Recipe navigation">
      <div class="sidebar-title">Browse</div>
      <div class="sidebar-search">
        <input
          id="recipeSearch"
          type="text"
          placeholder="Search recipes…"
          autocomplete="off"
        />
      </div>
      <div id="sidebarContent" class="text-muted">Loading…</div>
    </aside>

    <section>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header">
          <div>
            <div class="card-title">Ingredients</div>
            <div class="card-subtitle">Ingredients for the pie</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ingredients">
          <ul>
            <li>4 cups cauliflower florets (medium head), cored</li>
            <li>Salt and freshly ground black pepper</li>
            <li>½ cup Greek yogurt</li>
            <li>12 oz vegetable soy protein crumbles</li>
            <li>1 medium yellow onion, diced</li>
            <li>1½ cups frozen mixed vegetables</li>
            <li>½ cup canned diced tomatoes, drained</li>
            <li>1 cup low-fat, low-sodium vegetable broth</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon cornstarch</li>
            <li>3 tablespoons chopped fresh chives</li>
            <li>⅓ cup whole-wheat panko breadcrumbs</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header">
          <div>
            <div class="card-title">Procedure</div>
            <div class="card-subtitle">Step-by-step baking instructions</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="procedure">
          <ol>
            <li>Preheat the oven to 450° F. Line a baking sheet with foil and spray with cooking spray.</li>
            <li>Spread the cauliflower on the prepared sheet; season with salt and pepper. Top with another foil sheet and seal edges. Roast 20 minutes.</li>
            <li>Remove top foil carefully and roast until tender and beginning to brown, about an additional 10 minutes (oven remains at 450° F).</li>
            <li>Transfer cauliflower and Greek yogurt to a food processor; puree about 2 minutes until smooth. Season with salt and pepper. Cover to keep warm.</li>
            <li>Heat a large nonstick sauté pan over medium-high. Add soy protein crumbles, season to taste, and cook through. Drain if needed.</li>
            <li>Reduce heat to medium and add onion to the pan; sauté ~6 minutes until soft. Add frozen vegetables and diced tomatoes.</li>
            <li>In a small bowl, whisk broth with cornstarch. Add to the pan and simmer, stirring, until thickened (~2 minutes).</li>
            <li>Stir in chives and season to taste. Spread the vegetable mixture in an 8×8-inch glass baking dish.</li>
            <li>Top with cauliflower puree and sprinkle with panko breadcrumbs. Bake until hot throughout, about 8 minutes.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <hr class="soft" />

        <div class="card-info-box">
          <strong>Notes:</strong> Serve warm. Season with additional herbs if desired.
        </div>
      </div>

    </section>
  </main>

  <footer class="page-footer">
